    "body": "### Problem\n\ncursor is not placed at the bottom of cmdwin when entering it with `<c-f>`, if `cmdheight=0`\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/717309a4-ea2c-43b8-ba80-c1799d06ac02\n\nit's probably because of `splitkeep=screen` in ui2/cmdline.lua. removing it worked.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim -c \"se cmdheight=0 | lua require'vim._core.ui2'.enable()\" -u NONE\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ncursor at the bottom line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-748+gf50ec42da2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nmsi",
